Specify a value x > 0 if you want to add x additional diskfiles
to the database.

tbadmin will prompt for the properties, location etc. of the
additional diskfiles.

   -	Command Line Syntax :   dx=..
		The  dx=  syntax is the same as the d=  syntax
	Examples:
	$ tbadmin -a[f]  dbname  dx=
	   --> add 1 diskfile with default properties:
	$ tbadmin -a[f]  dbname  dx=,50000  dx=,30000,blob 
	   --> add 2 diskfiles with default location, and specific
	   sizes and the second reserved for BLOB's:
